---
@version: 2
@description: Specify minimum and maximum value for a value, and make sure that the value will not exceed the boundaries.
@lot:
- $value, [$min = 0, $max = null]
@example: |
  $A = b(40);
  $B = b(-35);
  $C = b(40, [0, 20]);
  $D = b(40, [0, 50]);
@result: |
  $A = 40;
  $B = 0;
  $C = 20;
  $D = 40;
...
